<recipe>
<title>
M&M Caramel Apples
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 5 minutes
COOK TIME: 10 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 15 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: apple, caramel
SERVINGS: 5 servings
</details>
<ingredients>
5 apples
1 11 oz. bag individually wrapped caramels, unwrapped
2 T. water
2 c. M&M'SÂ® Brand Chocolate Candies
</ingredients>
<instructions>
Push a popsicle stick into the core of each apple.
Bring a pot of water to boil.
Once at a boil, dip the apples in and quickly swirl around.
Remove apples, and let them dry.
Wipe off any wax or buildup.
In a separate pot, heat caramels and water over medium low, stirring frequently, until melted.
Dip apples in caramel, swirling to coat.
Let caramel sit for about 10 seconds.
Roll apples in M&M's, gently pressing them into the caramel.
Place apples on greased parchment or wax paper.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
</instructions>
</recipe>
